This paper deals with the problem of distance labeling, which is a fundamental topic in computer science and falls under the category of data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the hub labeling algorithm, which is used for finding shortest paths in large networks and involves graph theory (cs.CG). The reduction from the Vertex Cover problem suggests a connection to computational complexity theory (cs.CC) and the problem of finding optimal hub labeling involves optimization and combinatorics (cs.DM). Finally, the paper cites previous work on distance labeling on various graph classes, indicating a potential connection to graph theory (cs.GT).
